    public interface Axiom
    This interface is a part of the core of OWLOOP architecture. It contains interfaces of the basic components within OWLOOP. These components are used to define and give structure to a descriptor.

    The components are the following:

    • Axiom.Ground: is an OWL entity associated to an ontology.
    • Axiom.EntitySet: is a set of OWL entities associated to the Axiom.Ground via an expression.
    • Axiom.ExpressionEntity: associates an expression to the Axiom.EntitySet.
    • Axiom.ExpressionEntitySet: enables association of complex expressions to the Axiom.EntitySet.
    • Axiom.Descriptor: is in charge of mapping the (Axiom.Ground) and the (Axiom.EntitySet) via an (expression). A descriptor is also in charge of synchronizing them all, i.e, the axioms, between it's internal state and the OWL representation.
    • Axiom.MappingIntent: it keeps a record of the manipulations made by the Axiom.Descriptor during the synchronisation. While 'reading()' it records the changes made in the internal state of the descriptors, and while 'writing()' it records also the changes applied to the OWL representation.
